H0.text: Skin is the relatively thick covering of the main shaft of the penis.

H1.text: Bone is the relatively thick structure that covers the main shaft of the penis.

H2.text: Cellulose is the relatively thick covering of the main shaft of the penis.

H3.text: Collagen is the relatively thick material covering the main shaft of the penis.

A4.text: The epithelium of the penis consists of the shaft skin, the foreskin, and the preputial mucosa on the inside of the foreskin and covering the glans penis.
